x4freetext: Separated Sector Cyclotron (SSC) at
the iThemba Laboratory for Accelerator Based
Sciences (iThemba LABS), South Africa.
Self-supporting isotopically
enriched (more than 95%) 120Sn and 208Pb target foils
were used. The 208Pb target density was 2.1 mg/cm2
whereas two 120Sn targets were used, with densities
of 2.1 mg/cm2 and 3.32 mg/cm2.
The outgoing tritons were detected in the
focal plane detectors of the K = 600 QDD magnetic
spectrometer. The spectrometer has a 9.7% momentum
acceptance and +/-2 degree angular acceptance. The
detectors consisted of a pair of wire chambers
followed by a pair of plastic scintillators. The wire
chambers allowed for the reconstruction of particle
trajectories in the focal plane while the plastic
scintillators were used as trigger detectors and to
perform particle identification.
Information received from B.Mouginot 03 July 2012.
Statistical uncertainties of the tritons
detected the focal plane of the spectrometer.
Uncertainties of the incident proton
beam - 1%.
Uncertainty of the target thickness - 1%.
Cross section corresponds to an integration
over the angular acceptance of the spectrometer +/- 2
degree.
By B.Mouginot: Peaks were observed in some excitation
spectra around 15 MeV from the 16O(p,t) and at higher
energies from 12C(p,t) reactions due to target
contamination. Deuteron contamination from
120Sn(p,d)119Sn reaction can be observed on the
spectrum at 7 degree.
The point below 0 MeV correspond to experimental
measurement below the reaction threshold.
Data received from B.Mouginot, 28 June 2012.
Entry approved by B.Mouginot, 03 July 2012.
